The paper deals with the Shortest Superstring Problem (SSP), which is a well-known problem in computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms and their performance, which is related to the field of approximation algorithms (cs.DM). The specific application of SSP to next-generation sequencing (NGS) data suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of computational biology (cs.CG) and machine learning (cs.LG), as NGS data analysis often involves machine learning techniques.
